1. Modify the first variables in generate_handlers.sh to tell the script
   where the PHP sources can be found.

2. $ ./generate_handlers.sh

3. $ php generate_handler_lookup.php < /path/to/php5/Zend/zend_vm_execute.h

4. $ phpize

5. $ ./configure --enable-phpllvm

6. $ make && sudo make install

7. Copy "module_template.bc" to your current working directory before you run:

    $ php -dextension=phpllvm.so -dphpllvm.active=1 your_script.php

    After each execution, you can examine the generated LLVM in the current
    working directory with:

    $ llvm-dis -o - previous_execution.bc
